ExecDesc.value: Sophos Anti-Virus CAB Files Invalid typeCompress Parsing Heap Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Sophos Anti-Virus. The vulnerability is due to an error in the way the application handles invalid typeCompress value. The error causes the bounds check on the input data size being skipped, which further leads to a heap buffer overflow. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by causing Sophos Anti-Virus to process a specially crafted CAB file. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the affected service, which is SYSTEM by default.
